set.seed(29)
spartinatest <- read.csv("Spartina_TestData.csv")
spartinatest$Stem_Height_mm <- rnorm(120, mean = 370, sd = 158)

ht_data <- spartinatest %>%
  arrange(Stem_Height_mm) %>%
  mutate(Group = ntile(Stem_Height_mm, 12)) %>%
  
  mutate(
    Inundated = case_when(
      Group %in% 1:6 ~ "Yes",
      Group %in% 7:12 ~ "No"
    ),
    Soil_Treatment = case_when(
      Group %in% c(1, 2, 3, 7, 8, 9) ~ "Organic",
      Group %in% c(4, 5, 6, 10, 11, 12) ~ "Sand",
    ),
    Microbe_Treatment = case_when(
      Group %in% c(1, 7) ~ "None",
      Group %in% c(2, 8) ~ "SOB",
      Group %in% c(3, 9) ~ "Community",
      Group %in% c(4, 10) ~ "None",
      Group %in% c(5, 11) ~ "SOB",
      Group %in% c(6, 12) ~ "Community"
    )
  ) 

ht_data <- ht_data %>% mutate(Stem_Height_mm = if_else(Stem_Height_mm < 0, NA, Stem_Height_mm)) 
ht_data %>%
  group_by(Inundated, Soil_Treatment, Microbe_Treatment) %>%
  summarize(count = n(),
            mean = mean(Stem_Height_mm),
            sd = sd(Stem_Height_mm))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Inundated', 'Soil_Treatment'. You can
## override using the `.groups` argument.
## # A tibble: 12 × 6
## # Groups:   Inundated, Soil_Treatment [4]

## 10 Yes       Sand           Community            10  344.  8.37
## 11 Yes       Sand           None                 10  264. 20.9 
## 12 Yes       Sand           SOB                  10  318. 10.9
ht_data %>%
  group_by(Inundated, Soil_Treatment, Microbe_Treatment) %>%
  mutate(groups = paste(Inundated, Soil_Treatment, Microbe_Treatment, sep='_')) %>%
  
ggplot(aes(x = groups, y = Stem_Height_mm, color = groups, fill = groups)) +
  geom_violin(trim = FALSE) +  # Violin plot
  labs(
    title = "Stem Height by Treatment Group",
    x = "Treatment Group",
    y = "Stem Height (mm)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +  # Rotate x-axis labels
  scale_color_viridis_d() +  # Use a color palette
  facet_wrap(~ Microbe_Treatment)  # Facet by Microbe_Treatment

Belowground Biomass

set.seed(29)
bg_data <- rnorm(120, mean = 0.7104, sd = 0.4) %>% sort()  # Generate and sort values

# Assign Belowground_biomass_g based on Group rank
bg_data <- ht_data %>%
  mutate(
    Belowground_biomass_g = {
      group_order <- order(Group)  # Order plants by their Group
      bg_data[group_order]         # Assign sorted biomass to plants by Group rank
    },
    # Ensure non-negative values
    Belowground_biomass_g = if_else(Belowground_biomass_g < 0, NA, Belowground_biomass_g)
  )
bg_data %>%
  group_by(Inundated, Soil_Treatment, Microbe_Treatment) %>%
  summarize(count = n(),
            mean = mean(Belowground_biomass_g),
            sd = sd(Belowground_biomass_g))

Generalized Linear Models

Stem Height

sp_data_final <- sp_data_final %>%
  mutate(
    Inundated = as.factor(Inundated),
    Soil_Treatment = as.factor(Soil_Treatment),
    Microbe_Treatment = as.factor(Microbe_Treatment)
  )

# Fit GLM for Stem_Height_mm
stem_model <- glm(
  Stem_Height_mm ~ Inundated + Soil_Treatment + Microbe_Treatment,
  family = gaussian(link = "identity"),
  data = sp_data_final
)

# Display summary of the model

  Stem_Height_mm ~ Inundated + Soil_Treatment + Microbe_Treatment +
